title: L: Winds are Strong, Giants are Big & a Witch is a Witch (The Odyssey Part 4)
itunes:title: L: Winds are Strong, Giants are Big & a Witch is a Witch (The Odyssey Part 4)
itunes:subtitle: Aeolus, Laestrygonians, and the witch, Circe.
description:
Odysseus and his men visit Aeolus, keeper of the winds, the Laestrygonians, and finally land on the witch Circe's island of Aiaia.


CW/TW: far too many Greek myths involve assault. Given it's fiction, and typically involves gods and/or monsters, I'm not as deferential as I would be were I referencing the real thing.


Sources: The Odyssey, translated by Emily Wilson.


Attributions and licensing information for music used in the podcast can be found here: mythsbaby.com/sources-attributions.
